==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Toque
<hw>Toque</hw> <pr>(t⟦omac⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>toque</ets>; of Celtic origin; cf. W. <ets>toc</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind of cap worn in the 16th century, and copied in
modern fashions; -- called also <altname>toquet</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His velvet <qex>toque</qex> stuck as airily as ever upon the side
of his head.</q> <rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A variety of the bonnet
monkey.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toquet</ent>⟦br⟧
